  "texts": [
    "In this format, memory information is organized into lists, and the semantic of memory can be conveyed in an efficient and concise manner.",
    "For instance, GITM [16] stores action lists for sub-goals in a hierarchical tree structure.",
    "The hierarchical structure explicitly captures the relationships between goals and corresponding plans.",
    "RET-LLM [42] initially converts natural language sentences into triplet phrases, and subsequently stores them in memory.Remark.",
    "Here we only show several representative memory formats, but it is important to note that there are many uncovered ones, such as the programming code used by [38]."
  ],
